16
00:00:11,955 --> 00:00:12,071
http://hiqve.com

17
00:00:12,072 --> 00:00:12,189
http://hiqve.com/

18
00:00:12,190 --> 00:00:15,190
http://hiqve.com/

19
00:00:18,643 --> 00:00:20,769
<i>ANNOUNCER: Republic victory is at hand.</i>

20
00:00:20,854 --> 00:00:23,147
<i>Clone troopers,</i>
<i>under the command of the Jedi,</i>

21
00:00:23,231 --> 00:00:26,817
<i>have successfully invaded</i>
<i>the Separatist occupied world of Ryloth.</i>

22
00:00:27,068 --> 00:00:30,112
<i>Anakin Skywalker battles the enemies</i>
<i>in the skies,</i>

23
00:00:30,196 --> 00:00:32,698
<i>while Obi-Wan Kenobi frees villages</i>

24
00:00:32,782 --> 00:00:36,702
<i>from the grip of vile Separatist leader</i>
Wat Tambor.

25
00:00:36,786 --> 00:00:40,414
<i>Now, Jedi General Mace Windu</i>
<i>leads the attack on enemy lines</i>

26
00:00:40,498 --> 00:00:44,501
<i>in the final offensive</i>
<i>to liberate the capital city of Lessu.</i>

27
00:00:45,086 --> 00:00:46,628
(WEAPONS FIRING)

28
00:01:03,938 --> 00:01:05,397
MACE: Take cover.

29
00:01:09,486 --> 00:01:12,821
-We have stopped the enemy advance.
-Give me those.

30
00:01:14,491 --> 00:01:18,160
Good. Now order our cannon
to target their rear units.

31
00:01:18,661 --> 00:01:21,663
We'll box them in
and blast them to pieces.

32
00:01:27,337 --> 00:01:29,004
(GRUNTS) We're pinned down!

33
00:01:29,089 --> 00:01:31,840
Commander, bring out
the Lightning Squadron.

34
00:01:31,966 --> 00:01:33,759
I want Lightning up here now!

35
00:01:45,522 --> 00:01:48,315
Get the injured back!
I'm gonna clear the road!

36
00:02:02,288 --> 00:02:05,541
-Sir, the enemy is advancing again.
-Let me see.

37
00:02:06,209 --> 00:02:08,836
Find some cover. Move it. Let's go.

38
00:02:09,129 --> 00:02:10,546
(FIRING CONTINUES)

39
00:02:12,465 --> 00:02:13,882
She's all yours, General!

40
00:02:15,051 --> 00:02:17,052
We'll lead the way, Commander.

41
00:02:19,722 --> 00:02:20,889
Forward!

42
00:02:30,066 --> 00:02:32,734
Now that Jedi is leading the attack.

43
00:02:33,403 --> 00:02:35,070
This doesn't look good.

44
00:02:35,363 --> 00:02:37,573
Concentrate all your fire on those walkers.

45
00:02:42,078 --> 00:02:43,203
Did we get him?

46
00:02:53,631 --> 00:02:54,715
Should we run?

47
00:02:54,799 --> 00:02:56,175
(RUMBLING)

48
00:02:57,886 --> 00:02:59,720
It would be better if we just surrendered.

49
00:02:59,804 --> 00:03:00,971
(EXCLAIMS)

50
00:03:04,851 --> 00:03:06,143
(BEEPING)

51
00:03:17,655 --> 00:03:21,283
-How many men did we lose?
-Thirty-two, I think,

52
00:03:21,367 --> 00:03:23,660
including command crews
of three walkers.

53
00:03:23,995 --> 00:03:26,371
The good news is
General Kenobi has broken their lines.

54
00:03:26,456 --> 00:03:28,624
We can clear a path straight
to the capital now.

55
00:03:30,210 --> 00:03:31,543
<i>MACE: This battle was costly.</i>

56
00:03:33,755 --> 00:03:36,048
<i>We're going to need help to take the city.</i>

57
00:03:36,132 --> 00:03:39,301
The Republic is advancing faster
than I expected.

58
00:03:39,385 --> 00:03:42,221
I calculate they will reach the main gates
by morning.

59
00:03:42,305 --> 00:03:46,308
-I recommend we prepare our retreat.
-I will not retreat.

60
00:03:46,392 --> 00:03:49,770
That Jedi does not have the troops
to take this city.

61
00:03:49,812 --> 00:03:53,649
Bring our units inside the walls
and secure the bridge.

62
00:03:57,654 --> 00:03:59,821
<i>What's your progress, Skywalker?</i>

63
00:03:59,989 --> 00:04:02,950
<i>My fighters have secured control</i>
<i>of the space around Ryloth.</i>

64
00:04:02,992 --> 00:04:05,077
<i>We have the Separatists cruisers</i>
<i>on the run.</i>

65
00:04:05,161 --> 00:04:07,496
<i>Very good, General Skywalker.</i>

66
00:04:07,789 --> 00:04:10,082
Master Kenobi has taken
the Jixuan Desert,

67
00:04:10,166 --> 00:04:12,292
so the southern hemisphere is ours.

68
00:04:12,585 --> 00:04:16,129
<i>-Then it's almost over.</i>
-Not yet.

69
00:04:16,339 --> 00:04:18,340
The key position is the capital of Lessu.

70
00:04:18,466 --> 00:04:20,801
Our spies are certain
the Separatist leader, Wat Tambor,

71
00:04:20,843 --> 00:04:22,636
has his command center there.

72
00:04:22,679 --> 00:04:26,515
<i>When taken the city we have,</i>
<i>capture Tambor we must.</i>

73
00:04:26,641 --> 00:04:30,686
It's not going to be easy, Master.
Tambor has chosen his stronghold well.

74
00:04:30,812 --> 00:04:33,814
This plasma bridge is the only way
in or out.

75
00:04:34,107 --> 00:04:37,693
<i>I'm afraid a siege</i>
<i>could drag on indefinitely.</i>

76
00:04:37,777 --> 00:04:40,195
<i>My people have suffered so much already.</i>

77
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:43,657
<i>A plan you have to take the bridge,</i>
<i>Master Windu? Hmm?</i>

78
00:04:43,700 --> 00:04:45,784
With our forces stretched so thinly,

79
00:04:45,868 --> 00:04:48,036
I'm going to enlist the help
of the freedom fighters,

80
00:04:48,121 --> 00:04:50,122
led by Cham Syndulla.

81
00:04:50,206 --> 00:04:53,375
His fight against the droids has made him
a symbol of freedom for the people.

82
00:04:53,459 --> 00:04:57,713
<i>Cham Syndulla was a radical</i>
<i>before the war.</i>

83
00:04:58,131 --> 00:05:01,550
<i>-He is very unpredictable.</i>
<i>-He can't be trusted.</i>

84
00:05:02,051 --> 00:05:06,513
<i>I know Syndulla seeks to gain power.</i>
<i>We were political rivals.</i>

85
00:05:06,556 --> 00:05:09,016
I'll leave the politics to you, Senator.

86
00:05:09,058 --> 00:05:11,476
I'm gonna do whatever I can
to help these people.

87
00:05:11,561 --> 00:05:15,647
<i>Perhaps we could send you</i>
<i>Republic reinforcements instead.</i>

88
00:05:15,940 --> 00:05:19,359
<i>There are no reinforcements</i>
<i>available, Chancellor.</i>

89
00:05:19,444 --> 00:05:22,112
We can't win without Syndulla's help.

90
00:05:24,782 --> 00:05:26,366
(FOOTSTEPS THUDDING)

91
00:05:30,538 --> 00:05:33,290
RAZOR: What makes you think
the rebels are this way, General?

92
00:05:35,710 --> 00:05:37,252
What is it, sir?

93
00:05:37,503 --> 00:05:40,464
The resistance fighters ride creatures
native to this region.

94
00:05:40,757 --> 00:05:42,716
And these tracks are fresh.

95
00:05:46,429 --> 00:05:48,805
Which means they can't be that far.

96
00:05:50,933 --> 00:05:53,226
Isn't this the spot
where they were massacred?

97
00:05:53,394 --> 00:05:58,106
Looks like it was a hell of a fight. Hmm.
I wonder who put up these gravestones.

98
00:05:58,191 --> 00:05:59,316
(DISTANT ROAR)

99
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:00,942
Is that them?

100
00:06:05,782 --> 00:06:06,990
(BEEPING)

101
00:06:15,541 --> 00:06:19,961
<i>Your tactical droid has informed me</i>
<i>of the pitiful job you have done</i>

102
00:06:20,046 --> 00:06:22,839
<i>protecting our investment on Ryloth.</i>

103
00:06:23,591 --> 00:06:27,844
That droid exaggerates!
I have not lost yet.

104
00:06:27,929 --> 00:06:33,141
<i>You are no match for Master Windu.</i>
<i>Do not become greedy, Emir Tambor.</i>

105
00:06:33,810 --> 00:06:37,187
<i>Take what valuables you can</i>
<i>and destroy everything else.</i>

106
00:06:37,563 --> 00:06:42,109
-Everything?
<i>-We can put this defeat to political use.</i>

107
00:06:42,527 --> 00:06:46,196
<i>The charred ruins of Ryloth</i>
<i>will demonstrate to the galaxy</i>

108
00:06:46,447 --> 00:06:49,866
<i>the cost of a Republic victory.</i>

109
00:06:50,201 --> 00:06:51,701
As you wish.

110
00:07:00,920 --> 00:07:03,505
Keep on the lookout for that lost patrol.

111
00:07:03,673 --> 00:07:06,049
(FOOTSTEPS CREAKING)

112
00:07:07,301 --> 00:07:09,094
Did you hear that?

113
00:07:20,106 --> 00:07:22,190
I don't see anything.

114
00:07:22,483 --> 00:07:26,820
-Look, it's RB-551.
-No wonder he got blasted.

115
00:07:26,946 --> 00:07:30,407
He's one of those older models
programmed by a central computer.

116
00:07:30,575 --> 00:07:32,993
Not us, we're independent thinkers.

117
00:07:33,035 --> 00:07:34,161
-Roger, roger.
-Roger, roger.

118
00:07:34,203 --> 00:07:35,495
Roger, roger.

119
00:07:35,663 --> 00:07:37,456
(FOOTSTEPS CREAKING)

120
00:07:42,128 --> 00:07:47,757
-Why didn't we take them out, sir?
-I have a feeling the rebels will do it for us.

121
00:07:48,009 --> 00:07:49,509
(LASER GUNS FIRING)

122
00:07:49,594 --> 00:07:52,053
DROID 1: Look out! It's an ambush!
DROID 2: Help! It's the resistance!

123
00:07:52,138 --> 00:07:53,221
(ROARING)

124
00:07:53,264 --> 00:07:54,556
(DROID SCREAMS)

125
00:07:55,725 --> 00:07:57,767
(LIGHTSABER ACTIVATING)

126
00:07:58,769 --> 00:08:00,395
(WEAPONS FIRING)

127
00:08:14,911 --> 00:08:18,121
I was wondering when you'd find me,
Master Jedi.

128
00:08:18,206 --> 00:08:23,793
-General Syndulla, I've come for your help.
-What makes you think you'll get it?

129
00:08:26,172 --> 00:08:27,797
(FOOTSTEPS THUDDING)

130
00:08:29,842 --> 00:08:33,386
Emir Tambor,
our bombers are nearly ready for launch.

131
00:08:38,434 --> 00:08:41,686
And now,
I will ready your ship for evacuation.

132
00:08:41,771 --> 00:08:45,106
No, I am not yet ready to leave.

133
00:08:45,191 --> 00:08:48,985
In any case, we have a schedule to keep.
The ship will be ready.

134
00:09:07,296 --> 00:09:10,590
-Some hideout you have here.
-It has advantages.

135
00:09:12,426 --> 00:09:14,511
(GROWLING)

136
00:09:15,263 --> 00:09:19,766
We saw the graves of many of your people
in that battlefield as well.

137
00:09:20,434 --> 00:09:23,395
Together, we can prevent that
from happening again.

138
00:09:23,479 --> 00:09:26,022
Do you know why we were massacred,
Master Jedi?

139
00:09:26,357 --> 00:09:30,443
When the droids swept over Ryloth,
the Republic was unable to help us.

140
00:09:30,736 --> 00:09:33,989
We were forced to surrender,
and we came here unarmed.

141
00:09:34,490 --> 00:09:37,492
The Separatists brought tanks
to exterminate us.

142
00:09:37,577 --> 00:09:40,495
Hey, come here, boy.
Come on, don't leave.

143
00:09:40,538 --> 00:09:41,830
(GROWLING)

144
00:09:41,914 --> 00:09:43,707
See, there's nothing to be afraid of here.

145
00:09:43,791 --> 00:09:45,000
(ROARS)

146
00:09:45,042 --> 00:09:46,167
(LAUGHING)

147
00:09:46,210 --> 00:09:48,253
(SPEAKING TWI'LEKI)

148
00:09:48,337 --> 00:09:50,505
He says his blurrg may be ill-tempered,

149
00:09:50,590 --> 00:09:53,174
but she is much faster
than your riding machines.

150
00:09:53,593 --> 00:09:55,510
I don't know about that.

151
00:10:06,856 --> 00:10:08,857
What is this? A scratch?

152
00:10:10,359 --> 00:10:13,236
Gobi, get better. I need you.

153
00:10:13,362 --> 00:10:15,572
(SPEAKING TWI'LEKI)

154
00:10:15,865 --> 00:10:17,365
We have little food or drink,

155
00:10:17,408 --> 00:10:21,036
but it is our tradition to share
what we do have with our guests.

156
00:10:33,716 --> 00:10:36,676
Target every Twi'lek village in range.

157
00:10:36,719 --> 00:10:39,846
-The inhabited ones first.
-Of course.

158
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:51,232
(FOOTSTEPS THUDDING)

159
00:10:53,027 --> 00:10:55,236
Have our scouts reported in
from the village up ahead?

160
00:10:55,279 --> 00:10:56,863
The enemy has already pulled out, sir.

161
00:10:56,906 --> 00:10:59,574
Friendlies are all that's left,
mostly women and children.

162
00:10:59,617 --> 00:11:01,743
See if we can spare some rations.
They'll be hungry.

163
00:11:01,869 --> 00:11:02,952
(RADAR BEEPING)

164
00:11:03,079 --> 00:11:04,913
Sir, enemy ships are entering our sector.

165
00:11:10,252 --> 00:11:11,628
(RUMBLING)

166
00:11:11,754 --> 00:11:12,921
Damage report!

167
00:11:13,047 --> 00:11:15,423
There's no tactical damage, sir.
They didn't hit us.

168
00:11:15,466 --> 00:11:16,925
They bombed the village.

169
00:11:25,434 --> 00:11:27,394
(SIGHS) Make contact with General Windu.

170
00:11:30,439 --> 00:11:32,232
<i>(TRIBAL MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

171
00:11:36,112 --> 00:11:38,446
I hope you don't mind this.

172
00:11:38,989 --> 00:11:43,493
A little distraction goes far
to ease the burden of the war on my men.

173
00:11:43,619 --> 00:11:46,955
You have provided well for your men.
All your people.

174
00:11:47,498 --> 00:11:50,291
So why won't you help me free them
from this occupation?

175
00:11:50,334 --> 00:11:54,796
I don't trust Senator Taa,
his plans for our world after the war.

176
00:11:54,880 --> 00:11:58,466
The Republic will help you rebuild.
We won't abandon you.

177
00:11:58,676 --> 00:12:03,471
-Your troops will stay for security?
-For a while. To keep the peace.

178
00:12:03,806 --> 00:12:07,142
Another armed occupation
is not a free Ryloth!

179
00:12:07,643 --> 00:12:10,854
How long before I am fighting you,
Master Jedi?

180
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:13,189
(COMLINK BEEPING)

181
00:12:14,734 --> 00:12:15,859
What is it, Commander?

182
00:12:15,985 --> 00:12:17,902
<i>The droids have begun</i>
<i>a firebombing campaign.</i>

183
00:12:17,987 --> 00:12:20,822
<i>Several villages in our sector</i>
<i>have been destroyed, sir.</i>

184
00:12:31,500 --> 00:12:35,086
Make the arrangements.
I will speak to Senator Taa.

185
00:12:40,718 --> 00:12:42,343
Is this all of it?

186
00:12:42,428 --> 00:12:46,014
We are still awaiting two transports
from our southern base.

187
00:12:46,182 --> 00:12:48,558
-Should we depart without them?
-No!

188
00:12:48,684 --> 00:12:52,187
I will have every valuable on this rock
before I leave.

189
00:12:52,438 --> 00:12:55,356
<i>Emir Tambor, why haven't you evacuated?</i>

190
00:12:55,858 --> 00:13:00,028
Our exit strategy is taking more time
to implement.

191
00:13:00,112 --> 00:13:04,365
<i>I want you out of the city</i>
<i>before the Republic arrives.</i>

192
00:13:04,408 --> 00:13:07,076
<i>Once Master Windu has invaded</i>
<i>the capital,</i>

193
00:13:07,369 --> 00:13:09,370
<i>you will bomb it from afar.</i>

194
00:13:09,705 --> 00:13:12,624
<i>-Am I understood?</i>
-Yes, Count Dooku.

195
00:13:13,751 --> 00:13:17,045
You will not do anything
until I give the order.

196
00:13:17,421 --> 00:13:19,339
We have our orders, Emir.

197
00:13:25,805 --> 00:13:30,433
Senator Taa, so glad you could join us
from comfortable Coruscant.

198
00:13:30,643 --> 00:13:33,478
Our people have survived with only me.

199
00:13:33,687 --> 00:13:37,398
<i>I knew you would try to turn this</i>
<i>into a campaign to take power!</i>

200
00:13:37,733 --> 00:13:42,904
<i>Need I remind you that it is I</i>
<i>who Leads our people in the Senate?</i>

201
00:13:43,072 --> 00:13:46,407
And it is I who leads our people
here and now.

202
00:13:46,700 --> 00:13:49,327
There will be nothing left to lead
if you two refuse to work together.

203
00:13:49,411 --> 00:13:50,495
(COMLINK BEEPING)

204
00:13:50,579 --> 00:13:53,540
<i>-ANAKIN: General Windu, do you copy?</i>
-I hear you, Skywalker.

205
00:13:53,874 --> 00:13:57,210
My fighters are taking out the bombers
as fast as they can, Master Windu.

206
00:13:57,294 --> 00:13:58,419
But there are just too many.

207
00:13:58,504 --> 00:14:00,296
<i>I doubt we can stop them all.</i>

208
00:14:00,381 --> 00:14:02,757
<i>I suggest you get the people away</i>
<i>from the cities.</i>

209
00:14:02,842 --> 00:14:05,260
You must destroy
those bombers, Skywalker.

210
00:14:05,344 --> 00:14:08,054
-Then meet me at the capital.
<i>-I'll do what I can.</i>

211
00:14:08,722 --> 00:14:10,056
(FIRING)

212
00:14:14,687 --> 00:14:18,857
<i>What can the Separatists hope to gain</i>
<i>from burning our homes?</i>

213
00:14:19,233 --> 00:14:24,070
Nothing. Wat Tambor spoils for others
what he cannot possess.

214
00:14:24,154 --> 00:14:25,989
<i>Then we must act quickly.</i>

215
00:14:26,073 --> 00:14:28,700
Senator, your people are hesitant
to join us

216
00:14:28,784 --> 00:14:31,870
because they're worried
there will be another military occupation.

217
00:14:31,954 --> 00:14:34,747
<i>The people have my promise</i>

218
00:14:35,165 --> 00:14:41,004
<i>that the clone army will leave</i>
<i>once Ryloth is free of those droids.</i>

219
00:14:41,797 --> 00:14:45,258
General, what assurance
can you give Senator Taa

220
00:14:45,342 --> 00:14:47,135
you will not try to assume power?

221
00:14:47,511 --> 00:14:50,555
I only want to see my people free,
Master Jedi.

222
00:14:51,056 --> 00:14:54,267
I give my word. I believe in democracy.

223
00:14:56,520 --> 00:14:58,855
Then we are together in this.

224
00:15:02,985 --> 00:15:08,781
Men of Ryloth,
the time has come to free ourselves!

225
00:15:08,866 --> 00:15:10,450
(ALL CHEERING)

226
00:15:15,581 --> 00:15:16,998
(SIREN BLARING)

227
00:15:17,082 --> 00:15:21,169
They are deactivating the bridge.
Double time it, let's move!

228
00:15:21,795 --> 00:15:23,504
Get off the bridge!

229
00:15:27,843 --> 00:15:30,345
-Deactivate the bridge.
-Roger, roger.

230
00:15:30,679 --> 00:15:31,971
(POWERING DOWN)

231
00:15:32,014 --> 00:15:33,139
What the...

232
00:15:33,182 --> 00:15:34,599
(SCREAMING)

233
00:15:36,018 --> 00:15:40,980
-What about the city inhabitants?
-Drive them outside, but not too far.

234
00:15:41,357 --> 00:15:45,735
The Jedi will reconsider an attack
when he sees them in his line of fire.

235
00:16:03,712 --> 00:16:05,213
Keep moving.

236
00:16:10,302 --> 00:16:12,053
Try and keep up, clone!

237
00:16:12,221 --> 00:16:13,471
(URGES BEAST)

238
00:16:23,273 --> 00:16:24,899
Tambor is still there.

239
00:16:25,150 --> 00:16:28,236
SYNDULLA: How are we going to
attack with my people so close?

240
00:16:28,737 --> 00:16:30,154
MACE: Your people will never be in danger

241
00:16:30,239 --> 00:16:32,740
if our walkers can cross the bridge
into the city.

242
00:16:33,075 --> 00:16:35,827
Key is getting control of that bridge.

243
00:16:37,079 --> 00:16:38,955
Perhaps there is your way.

244
00:16:42,918 --> 00:16:45,837
My spies tell me
those transports carry treasure.

245
00:16:46,255 --> 00:16:49,340
It's not enough for the Separatists
to enslave and murder us.

246
00:16:49,675 --> 00:16:51,050
They must rob us, too.

247
00:16:51,427 --> 00:16:53,636
You think we can use them
to get across the bridge?

248
00:16:53,762 --> 00:16:56,764
It is risky.
They are usually scanned while crossing.

249
00:17:08,110 --> 00:17:11,320
When I get control of the bridge,
you must start the attack.

250
00:17:12,781 --> 00:17:14,782
(LIGHTSABER ACTIVATING)

251
00:17:23,876 --> 00:17:25,793
They're in. Let's go!

252
00:17:29,381 --> 00:17:30,798
(ROARING)

253
00:17:34,178 --> 00:17:36,971
Commander, I'll need you
to create a diversion.

254
00:17:37,222 --> 00:17:39,891
<i>-Get the rest of Lightning Squadron ready.</i>
-Yes, sir.

255
00:17:40,017 --> 00:17:41,142
(COMLINK BEEPS)

256
00:17:41,226 --> 00:17:42,477
My men are ready.

257
00:17:47,232 --> 00:17:48,858
It is time to leave.

258
00:17:48,984 --> 00:17:52,070
The Republic walkers are holding
at 1,200 meters.

259
00:17:52,905 --> 00:17:55,990
Sir, the last shipments of treasure
are approaching.

260
00:17:56,075 --> 00:17:57,617
Just in time.

261
00:17:57,701 --> 00:18:00,912
Activate the bridge
and get them across immediately.

262
00:18:01,413 --> 00:18:03,748
Initiating plasma projectors.

263
00:18:28,398 --> 00:18:30,691
(SCANNERS BUZZING)

264
00:18:34,822 --> 00:18:38,825
All right, hold it there.
Let's go, the boss wants this done.

265
00:18:50,587 --> 00:18:52,130
This one's all clear.

266
00:18:52,381 --> 00:18:53,548
Here they come.

267
00:18:54,550 --> 00:18:55,758
(LOUD BUZZING)

268
00:18:55,843 --> 00:18:58,594
Wait. I'm picking up an anomaly in there.

269
00:18:59,221 --> 00:19:00,680
Stay alert.

270
00:19:07,146 --> 00:19:08,855
Trooper, prepare to fire!

271
00:19:09,690 --> 00:19:11,566
Open the cargo hatch!

272
00:19:14,778 --> 00:19:16,904
-Oh, no!
-You're under arrest. You and the...

273
00:19:16,947 --> 00:19:18,489
(DROID SCREAMING)

274
00:19:18,574 --> 00:19:20,408
We're under attack!

275
00:19:22,995 --> 00:19:24,954
(LIGHTSABER WHOOSHING)

276
00:19:25,581 --> 00:19:29,000
-Deactivate the bridge!
-Oh, well, too bad for them.

277
00:19:29,084 --> 00:19:30,168
(SIREN BLARING)

278
00:19:30,252 --> 00:19:32,837
Run for it! They're turning the bridge off!

279
00:19:51,565 --> 00:19:52,773
(SCREAMS)

280
00:20:01,366 --> 00:20:05,119
-I'll hold them off. Get that bridge back up!
-Sir, yes, sir!

281
00:20:06,288 --> 00:20:07,747
Charge!

282
00:20:36,151 --> 00:20:39,237
-Hey, you're not authorized!
-Save it!

283
00:20:39,821 --> 00:20:40,947
(EXCLAIMS)

284
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:44,325
The bridge is up, sir.

285
00:20:52,834 --> 00:20:54,252
(RUMBLING)

286
00:21:00,509 --> 00:21:01,968
(CHEERING)

287
00:21:07,808 --> 00:21:09,308
(WEAPONS FIRING)

288
00:21:09,685 --> 00:21:12,937
You take these droids!
I'll go find Wat Tambor!

289
00:21:22,531 --> 00:21:24,031
(ROARS)

290
00:21:40,215 --> 00:21:44,635
Start my ship. That Tambor is a fool.

291
00:21:53,228 --> 00:21:54,562
My ship!

292
00:21:59,276 --> 00:22:03,237
I'm afraid Emir Tambor refused
to retreat in time.

293
00:22:03,280 --> 00:22:05,948
<i>That is unfortunate.</i>

294
00:22:06,575 --> 00:22:09,744
<i>Order our bombers</i>
<i>to destroy the capital immediately.</i>

295
00:22:21,089 --> 00:22:22,715
Surrender.

296
00:22:22,799 --> 00:22:26,510
General Windu,
perhaps we can come to a compromise.

297
00:22:26,720 --> 00:22:29,013
Not when I hold all the cards.

298
00:22:29,097 --> 00:22:32,391
It appears a surrender is unnecessary.

299
00:22:32,476 --> 00:22:35,978
We will all perish for the glory
of the Separatists' alliance.

300
00:22:43,987 --> 00:22:45,071
Whoa!

301
00:22:45,113 --> 00:22:48,240
-That was close, Master.
-Isn't it always, Snips?

302
00:22:51,787 --> 00:22:55,915
-What are your terms for surrender?
-They're unconditional.

303
00:22:57,751 --> 00:22:59,043
Agreed.

304
00:22:59,961 --> 00:23:04,632
I thank you, Master Jedi.
Today, all of Ryloth thanks you.

305
00:23:05,550 --> 00:23:08,594
You've earned your freedom, General.
All of you.

306
00:23:08,618 --> 00:23:10,618
http://hiqve.com/

